<title>USA: U.S. HEADLINE STOCKS - Issues to watch - June 18.</title>
<headline>U.S. HEADLINE STOCKS - Issues to watch - June 18.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-06-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Stocks to watch this morning:</p>
<p>-- PanCanadian Petroleum Ltd said it agreed to buy CS Resources Ltd for $521 million.</p>
<p>-- Loral and France's Alcatel Alsthom said they would form a strategic alliance in multimedia satellite networks.</p>
<p>-- Seagate Technology Inc, a maker of disk drives, said it sees fourth-quarter results falling short of expectations.  </p>
<p>-- Gateway 2000 said it expects second-quarter results to be flat with those of the first quarter due to weaker demand.</p>
<p>-- Oracle Corp posted fourth-quarter earnings of $359.9 million, or $0.54 per share, up from $266.3 million, or $0.40 per share, a year earlier. Revenues rose 33 percent to $1.95 billion.</p>
<p>-- Fidelity Investments is expected to announce the layoff of 280 to 300 people, the Wall Street Journal reported.</p>
<p>-- RJR Nabisco's R.J. Reynolds has sued the Federal Trade Commission over the agency's efforts to ban the Joe Camel character, the Wall Street Journal said.</p>
<p>((--Wall Street Desk, 212-859-1730))</p>
